prettier-vue-syntax-parsing-robustness:
Thank you.

It is unsafe to use TS parser always. For example, The below code is valid as JS and TS.

```ts
const foo = doSomething<T1 | T2>(param)
```

```js
// as JS
const foo = (doSomething < T1) | (T2 > param);
```

TS and JS parse differently for such codes. Therefore, it is safe to parse as TypeScript only when the script tag explicitly specifies the use of TS.

