opentofu-separate-configuration-lifecycl:
1. It's more so a "provider block" vs "provider block with instance data"
2. This is true, the expansion here feels a bit weird IMO and I noticed that during the prototype phase.  This change is the "low churn" option, but adds cognitive load to understanding provider configs in the configs package. 

There are technically 3 levels of config parsing that are all mixed together:
1. hcl/json text -> configs.File (HCL loading)
2. configs.File -> configs.Module (merging files)
3. configs.Module -> configs.Module (static evaluation)

Even before static evaluation was added, there were all sorts of odd validation bugs all throughout the code when dealing with overrides.  Static evaluation shines more of a light on this.

In this specific scenario, we would need:
```go

// File parsing produces
type configs.ProviderBlock struct {
  // 1-1 mapping to HCL
}

// Module struct from Files (normal+override) produces
type configs.ProviderData struct {
  // Closer to existing struct
  ForEach hcl.Expression
  Count hcl.Expression
}
// Validation is performed when constructing ProviderData

// func (ProviderData) expand(StaticContext) []Provider

// Expanded into one or more
type configs.Provider struct {
  // Matches existing struct
  
  ForEachValue *cty.Value
  CountValue *cty.Value
  // OR
